acBoard.description: AudioCodes Proprietary MIB Contains The managed objects of AudioCodes systems. Through this MIB, the User can set up the board configuration parameters, reset the board, and monitor the board's operational robustness and quality of service during run-time. This MIB has the following Groups: boardConfiguration boardInformation channelConfiguration channelStatus notifications reset boardConfiguration: When The user Get Parameter from most of sub-groups in boardConfiguration group, he gets the value that should be burned to the board after the next Remote Reset. He can Set new values to many parameters, and these values will burned to the board after the next remote Reset In the sub-group mGCPDefaultChannelSettings the parameters are the actual parameters, that will take place when opening channel. (Reset is not needed for that sub-group). BoardInformation: Contains Read-only parameters like: board name, serial number, number of channels, software version. ChannelConfiguration: Read-only Parameters to see the configuratin of each channel: voice settings, fax settings, etc. ChannelStatus: Read-only parameters about the status of channel, like: Is the channle active, is it in Silence Period, is it in Fax mode, ON/Off hook, etc. This group contains also counters: packets to DSP, errors, lost packets, underruns, etc. Notifications: In this version, the notification we have are: acEvBoardStarted, and acEvResetingBoard. The board should send these notifications to its manager that the user defined in INI file with the parameter: NMPManagerIP = (IP address). Reset: To remote reset the board, the user should set an integer value to the parameter remoteReset. Then he should get the trap acEvResettingBoard. Note: Before Reset, The current boardConfiguration parameters will be burned to the board. The user should not use INI file, if he wants these parameters to take place. To set the default values, the user should set an integer value to the parameter acSetDefaults.

pCMLawSelect.name: pCMLawSelect
pCMLawSelect.description: Selects the type of PCM companding law in input/output TDM bus (TDM bus is defined using the TDMBusType parameter).

tDMBusClockSource.name: tDMBusClockSource
tDMBusClockSource.description: Selects the clock source on which the board synchronizes

tDMBusEnableFallBack.name: tDMBusEnableFallBack
tDMBusEnableFallBack.description: Enable/Disable clock fallback. The Fall Back clock is determined by BSPTDMBusFallbackClock

tDMBusLocalReference.name: tDMBusLocalReference
tDMBusLocalReference.description: When ClockSource is set to acH110BusClockSource_Network this parameter selects the TrunkID to be used as the clock synchronization source of the board. When using H.110/H.100 bus this parameter also selects the trunk which is used as the clock source for the NETREF clock generation (in this case ClockSource might not be set to acH110BusClockSource_Network).

idlePCMPattern.name: idlePCMPattern
idlePCMPattern.description: PCM Pattern applied to E1/T1 timeslot (B-channel) when channel is idle.

idleABCD.name: idleABCD
idleABCD.description: ABCD (CAS) Pattern to be applied to CAS signaling bus before changed by the user or PSTN protocol. This is only relevant when using PSTN interface with CAS protocols.

tDMBusMasterSlaveSelection.name: tDMBusMasterSlaveSelection
tDMBusMasterSlaveSelection.description: Set SC/MVIP/H.110 to either: Master mode (the board is the clock source for the TDM bus) or Slave mode (some other board in the system must supply the clock to the TDM bus).

tDMBusNetRefSpeed.name: tDMBusNetRefSpeed
tDMBusNetRefSpeed.description: Determine the NetRef frequency (for both generation and synchronization).

tDMBusOutputStartingChannel.name: tDMBusOutputStartingChannel
tDMBusOutputStartingChannel.description: Defines the outgoing TDM Timeslot of the first channel (ChannelId=0). The remaining channels are organized sequentially.

boardTDMBusOutputPort.name: boardTDMBusOutputPort
boardTDMBusOutputPort.description: Defines the SC/MVIP/H.100/H.110 port to be used for board's channel #0. All other channels then occupy the next timeslots sequentially

tDMBusSpeed.name: tDMBusSpeed
tDMBusSpeed.description: Selects the TDM Bus Speed. Speed is set according to the Bus Type. The following are allowed speeds for each bus type: SC = 0/2/3 H.110/H.100 = 3 MVIP = 0

tDMBusType.name: tDMBusType
tDMBusType.description: Selects the TDM bus interface to be used (only one TDM bus interface can be enabled at one time although more than one can physically exist on the board).

acOverrideDefaultIdlePCMPattern.name: acOverrideDefaultIdlePCMPattern
acOverrideDefaultIdlePCMPattern.description: Override Default Idle PCM Pattern. 0 - use defaults (0xff-Mulaw, 0x55-Alaw) 1 - use IdlePCMPattern.

acOverrideDefaultIdleABCDPattern.name: acOverrideDefaultIdleABCDPattern
acOverrideDefaultIdleABCDPattern.description: Description: Override Default Idle ABCD Pattern. 0 - use defaults (0xf) 1 - use IdleABCDPattern.

baseUDPPort.name: baseUDPPort
baseUDPPort.description: Lower boundary of UDP ports to be used by the board. The upper boundary is BoardBaseUDPPort+10*(Number of Channels). Must be a multiple of 10.

defaultGatewayAddr.name: defaultGatewayAddr
defaultGatewayAddr.description: Default Gateway Address. Board's Default Gateway IP address. (in host byte order e.g. 192.10.1.255 = 0xc00a01ff).

boardIPAddr.name: boardIPAddr
boardIPAddr.description: Board IP Address. in host byte order e.g. 192.10.1.2 = 0xc00a0102). Users should set the subnet mask to a valid value per the IP address.

boardSubNetAddr.name: boardSubNetAddr
boardSubNetAddr.description: Board SubNet Address. (in host byte order e.g. 255.255.255.0 = 0xffffff00). default =255.255.255.0.

acSyslogServerIP.name: acSyslogServerIP
acSyslogServerIP.description: IP address in dotted format notation, e.g., 192.10.1.255

acMGControlProtocolType.name: acMGControlProtocolType
acMGControlProtocolType.description: This parameter defines the control protocol type 0 = none, 1 = MGCP, 2 = MEGACO, 4 = H323, 8 = SIP

acDisableWEBConfig.name: acDisableWEBConfig
acDisableWEBConfig.description: Enables or disables Web Configuration 0-Read & Write mode(default) 1-Read Only mode

acContrlProtocolTransportType.name: acContrlProtocolTransportType
acContrlProtocolTransportType.description: Defines the transport type for the control: 0 - UDP, 1 - TCP (SCTP on road map).

acCPControlDiffServ.name: acCPControlDiffServ
acCPControlDiffServ.description: Defines the value of the 'DiffServ' field in the IP header for the control session.

snmpManagerIsUsed.name: snmpManagerIsUsed
snmpManagerIsUsed.description: Enable the SNMP Manager to recieve traps.

snmpManagerIp.name: snmpManagerIp
snmpManagerIp.description: IP address of default SNMP manager in dotted notation format: xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx. SNMP traps are sent to this manager.

snmpManagerTrapPort.name: snmpManagerTrapPort
snmpManagerTrapPort.description: Sets the trap ports to be used by the different managers.

snmpManagerTrapSendingEnable.name: snmpManagerTrapSendingEnable
snmpManagerTrapSendingEnable.description: Enable the SNMP Manager to recieve traps.

acNTPUtcOffset.name: acNTPUtcOffset
acNTPUtcOffset.description: NTP time to offset in seconds. Default is 0. Range - Between -43200 ot 43200 seconds.

acNTPUpdateInterval.name: acNTPUpdateInterval
acNTPUpdateInterval.description: NTPupdate interval in seconds. Default is 86400 (24 hours). Not recommended to be set beyond one month (2592000 sec).

enableDiagnostics.name: enableDiagnostics
enableDiagnostics.description: The EnableDiagnostics checks the correct functionality of different hardware components on the board. Upon completion, the board sends EV_END_BIT which contains information on the results of the test of each hardware component.

trunkId.name: trunkId
trunkId.description: Trunk ID at board in which the call is taking place

clockMaster.name: clockMaster
clockMaster.description: Selects the trunk clock source. When choosing acCLOCK_MASTER_OFF (= 0) the clock is recovered from the line. When choosing acCLOCK_MASTER_ON (= 1) the trunk clock source is provided by the internal/TDM bus clock source depending on the TDMBusClockSource parameter.

framingMethod.name: framingMethod
framingMethod.description: Selects the Framing method to be used for this trunk.

protocolType.name: protocolType
protocolType.description: Protocol Type. Sets the PSTN protocol to be used for this trunk. The protocol type parameter defines the interface and the specific telephony protocol. Each protocol defines the following: 1. E1 or T1 physical line configuration. 2. Fixed connection of the relevant time-slots, which are the Trunks' B-channels, mapping to the 60 (128 for TrunkPack-VoIP/400) DSP channels. This limitation is about to change in versions higher than 3.4. 3. Layer 3 specific telephony protocol or transparent mode of operation. Currently only identical configurations (protocol type, framing method, etc.) for the two trunks are supported.(see at the TrunkPack-VoIP User Manual for available protocols families) relevant only when TDMBusType=FRAMERS.

terminationSide.name: terminationSide
terminationSide.description: For ISDN only. select the ISDN Termination side (layer 2)

dchConfig.name: dchConfig
dchConfig.description: Defines D-channel configuration. This setting is only applicable to ISDN PRI protocols that support NFAS and/or D-channel backup procedures.

lineCode.name: lineCode
lineCode.description: Use to select line code. B8ZS or AMI for T1 spans and HDB3 or AMI for E1 spans.

lineBuildOutLoss.name: lineBuildOutLoss
lineBuildOutLoss.description: Selects the line build out loss to be used for this trunk

lineBuildOutOverwrite.name: lineBuildOutOverwrite
lineBuildOutOverwrite.description: Overwrite the framer's XPM registers values (these registers control the line pulse shape).

lineBuildOutXPM0.name: lineBuildOutXPM0
lineBuildOutXPM0.description: Controls the Framer's XPM0 register value (line pulse shape control). Applicable only when TrunkConfig.LineBuildOut.Overwrite=1.Should be used only by expert Users.

lineBuildOutXPM1.name: lineBuildOutXPM1
lineBuildOutXPM1.description: Controls the Framer's XPM1 register value (line pulse shape control). Applicable only when TrunkConfig.LineBuildOut.Overwrite=1. Should be used only by expert Users.

lineBuildOutXPM2.name: lineBuildOutXPM2
lineBuildOutXPM2.description: Controls the Framer's XPM2 register value (line pulse shape control). Applicable only when TrunkConfig.LineBuildOut.Overwrite=1.Should be used only by expert Users.

acV5InterfaceTrunkGroupId.name: acV5InterfaceTrunkGroupId
acV5InterfaceTrunkGroupId.description: copy from Table 8-1 in LIB manual 4.2beta

acV5LinkIdOld.name: acV5LinkIdOld
acV5LinkIdOld.description: copy from Table 8-1 in LIB manual 4.2beta

acIsdnNfasInterfaceId.name: acIsdnNfasInterfaceId
acIsdnNfasInterfaceId.description: Defines the Interface ID works with NS_EXPLICIT_INTERFACE_ID bit. Refer to the Appendix A.8 'ISDN Flexible Behavior' in the VoPLib Reference Library User's Manual Document #: LTRT-00740.

acTrunkCasTableIndex.name: acTrunkCasTableIndex
acTrunkCasTableIndex.description: Index of Cas Table used by this Trunk

acIsdnQ931LayerResponseBehavior.name: acIsdnQ931LayerResponseBehavior
acIsdnQ931LayerResponseBehavior.description: Bit-field used to determine several behavior options, which influence how the Q.931 protocol behaves.

acIsdnIncomingCallsBehavior.name: acIsdnIncomingCallsBehavior
acIsdnIncomingCallsBehavior.description: This is the bit-field used to determine several behavior options that influence how the ISDN Stack INCOMING calls behave. Refer to the Appendix A.8 'ISDN Flexible Behavior' in the VoPLib Reference Library User's Manual Document #: LTRT-00740.

acIsdnOutgoingCallsBehavior.name: acIsdnOutgoingCallsBehavior
acIsdnOutgoingCallsBehavior.description: This is the bit-field used to determine several behavior options that influence how the ISDN Stack OUTGOING calls behave. Refer to Appendix A.8 in the 'VoPLib Reference Library User's Manual.

acIsdnGeneralCCBehavior.name: acIsdnGeneralCCBehavior
acIsdnGeneralCCBehavior.description: This is the bit-field used to determine several general ISDN behavior options. Refer to the Appendix A.8 'ISDN Flexible Behavior' in the VoPLib Reference Library User's Manual Document #: LTRT-00740.

acIsdnNfasGroupNumber.name: acIsdnNfasGroupNumber
acIsdnNfasGroupNumber.description: Relevant only for T1 ISDN NFAS trunks indicates the group number of the NFAS group. ;Valid NFAS group numbers are only 1 to 4, 0 indicating that this trunk is not NFAS (in this case the ISDNNFASInterfaceID and DchConfig parameters are ignored).

callAgentIP.name: callAgentIP
callAgentIP.description: MGCP Call Agent IP address to be used for the initial RestartInProgress MGCP message (RSIP) (e.g., 192.10.1.255). Set to 0.0.0.0 to avoid sending RSIP. This parameter if in use overrides the Call Agent IP address provided in BootP.

callAgentPort.name: callAgentPort
callAgentPort.description: Gate Way will use CallAgentPort as default UDP Port of MGCP Call Agent.

redundantAgentIP.name: redundantAgentIP
redundantAgentIP.description: Redundant MGCP call agent IP address for initial RestartInProgress MGCP message (RSIP) e.g. 192.10.1.255. Set to 0 to avoid sending RSIP.

redundantAgentPort.name: redundantAgentPort
redundantAgentPort.description: UDP Port of Redundant MGCP call agent.

redundantCallAgentDomainName.name: redundantCallAgentDomainName
redundantCallAgentDomainName.description: Redundant MGCP Call Agent Domain name

dePopulatedChannelsNumber.name: dePopulatedChannelsNumber
dePopulatedChannelsNumber.description: This parameter can be used to enable MGCP call agent to access only subset of the on board channel bank. Set to -1 (or do not specify) to use all channels.

endPointName.name: endPointName
endPointName.description: MGCP: Gateway's end point name. This is a prefix used to identify the endpoint, i.e., 'ACgw' in the following example: 'ACgw5@acl.com'. MEGACO: Prefix of the endpoint part of the termination name

mGCPCommunicationLayerTimeout.name: mGCPCommunicationLayerTimeout
mGCPCommunicationLayerTimeout.description: Assumed delay of the communication layer. It is used in retransmission.

acChDefaultDJBufOptFactor.name: acChDefaultDJBufOptFactor
acChDefaultDJBufOptFactor.description: Dynamic Jitter Buffer frame error/delay optimization.

acChDefaultCallerIDType.name: acChDefaultCallerIDType
acChDefaultCallerIDType.description: The supported caller ID standard types

acChDefaultFaxModemBypassM.name: acChDefaultFaxModemBypassM
acChDefaultFaxModemBypassM.description: Number of basic frames to generating one RTP fax/modem bypass packet.

acChDefaultFaxModemRelayVolume.name: acChDefaultFaxModemRelayVolume
acChDefaultFaxModemRelayVolume.description: Fax gain control. The range -18 to -3 relates to -18.5 dBm to -3.5 dBm in 1 dBm steps.

acChDefaultFaxRelayECMEnable.name: acChDefaultFaxRelayECMEnable
acChDefaultFaxRelayECMEnable.description: Enables or disables the using of ECM mode during Fax Relay.

acChDefaultFaxRelayMaxRate.name: acChDefaultFaxRelayMaxRate
acChDefaultFaxRelayMaxRate.description: Limits the maximum rate at which fax messages are transmitted.

acChDefaultFaxTransportMode.name: acChDefaultFaxTransportMode
acChDefaultFaxTransportMode.description: Sets the Fax over IP transport method.

acChDefaultModemRelayRedundancyDepth.name: acChDefaultModemRelayRedundancyDepth
acChDefaultModemRelayRedundancyDepth.description: Amount of redundancy for fax relay packets

acChDefaultUseT38orFRF11.name: acChDefaultUseT38orFRF11
acChDefaultUseT38orFRF11.description: Selects protocol to send/ receive fax relay.

acChDefaultV21ModemTransportType.name: acChDefaultV21ModemTransportType
acChDefaultV21ModemTransportType.description: Sets the V.21 modem transport method (must be set to 0 = disable)

acChDefaultV22ModemTransportType.name: acChDefaultV22ModemTransportType
acChDefaultV22ModemTransportType.description: Sets the V.22 modem transport method

acChDefaultV23ModemTransportType.name: acChDefaultV23ModemTransportType
acChDefaultV23ModemTransportType.description: Sets the V.23 modem transport method

acChDefaultV32ModemTransportType.name: acChDefaultV32ModemTransportType
acChDefaultV32ModemTransportType.description: Sets the V.32 modem transport method

acChDefaultV34ModemTransportType.name: acChDefaultV34ModemTransportType
acChDefaultV34ModemTransportType.description: Sets the V.34 modem transport method

acChDefaultFaxModemBypassCoderType.name: acChDefaultFaxModemBypassCoderType
acChDefaultFaxModemBypassCoderType.description: The User can set the bypass coder (according to the known coders)

acChDefaultFaxRelayRedundancyDepth.name: acChDefaultFaxRelayRedundancyDepth
acChDefaultFaxRelayRedundancyDepth.description: Default: Fax Relay Redundancy Depth. Number of repetitions to be applied to each fax relay payload when transmitting to network.

acChDefaultT38ProtectionMode.name: acChDefaultT38ProtectionMode
acChDefaultT38ProtectionMode.description: Default: T38 Protection Mode. Use Forward Error Correction (FEC) algorithm to protect T.38 fax relay stream.

acChDefaultDTMFTransportType.name: acChDefaultDTMFTransportType
acChDefaultDTMFTransportType.description: 0 = Mute = erases digit from voice stream does not relay to remote. 2 = Transparent = digits remains in voice stream. 3 = RFC 2833 relay = erase digit from voice stream relay to remote using RFC 2833 syntax. The other values as seen in the Value List (1 and 7) are not supported as of version 4.4.

acChDefaultMFTransportType.name: acChDefaultMFTransportType
acChDefaultMFTransportType.description: 0 = erase MFs from voice transport not relayed to remote. 2 = MFs not erased not relayed to remote. 3 = MFs are muted from the voice stream & relayed according to RFC 2833.

acChDefaultInputGain.name: acChDefaultInputGain
acChDefaultInputGain.description: PCM input gain. The range is 31 dB to +31 dB in 1 dB steps.

acChDefaultRTPRedundancyDepth.name: acChDefaultRTPRedundancyDepth
acChDefaultRTPRedundancyDepth.description: Enables or disables generation of RFC 2198 redundancy packets.

acChDefaultTestMode.name: acChDefaultTestMode
acChDefaultTestMode.description: Testing mode applied. 0 = Coder Loopback performs an encoder/decoder loopback inside DSP device. 1 = PCMLoopback loops back incoming PCM to the outgoing PCM. 2 = ToneInjection generates a 1000 Hz tone to outgoing PCM. 3 = NoLoopback sets the channel to work in normal mode.

acChDefaultVoiceVolume.name: acChDefaultVoiceVolume
acChDefaultVoiceVolume.description: Voice output gain control the range is -31 dB to +31 dB in 1 dB steps -32 = mute.

acChDefaultM.name: acChDefaultM
acChDefaultM.description: Number of DSP payloads for generating one RTP packet

acChDefaultDTMFDetectionPoint.name: acChDefaultDTMFDetectionPoint
acChDefaultDTMFDetectionPoint.description: Defines if the detection of DTMF events is notified at the end of DTMF or at the start of DTMF.

acChDefaultRtpIpTos.name: acChDefaultRtpIpTos
acChDefaultRtpIpTos.description: Sets value of IP Type Of Service field in IP header for all packets generated from this channel. Follow the acTIPTOS enumeration.

acChDefaultRtpIpPrecedence.name: acChDefaultRtpIpPrecedence
acChDefaultRtpIpPrecedence.description: Sets value of the IP precedence field in the IP header for all packets generated from this channel. Follow the acTIPPrecedence enumeration.

acChDefaultEchoCancler.name: acChDefaultEchoCancler
acChDefaultEchoCancler.description: Controls the activation of the Echo Canceler (refer also to 'ForceEchoOff')

acChDefaultEchoCanclerHybridLoss.name: acChDefaultEchoCanclerHybridLoss
acChDefaultEchoCanclerHybridLoss.description: Sets worst case ratio between signal level transmitted to hybrid & echo level returning from hybrid. Set this per worst hybrid in the system in terms of echo return loss. Refer to acTECHybridLoss enumeration:

vPMask.name: vPMask
vPMask.description: VP masking bits used for address resolution

vCMask.name: vCMask
vCMask.description: VC masking bits used for address resolution

externalClk.name: externalClk
externalClk.description: Source clock of on the board UTOPIA bus

aTMLoopBack.name: aTMLoopBack
aTMLoopBack.description: Phy loopback. The loopback can be used for testing purposes. The loopback direction is towards the PSTN side

utopiaSlave.name: utopiaSlave
utopiaSlave.description: UTOPIA interface mode of bus arbitration

multyPhy.name: multyPhy
multyPhy.description: UTOPIA interface SinglePhy or MultiPhy mode

slavePhyNum.name: slavePhyNum
slavePhyNum.description: Provides the slave number for this device (board) in the UTOPIA system bus (Applies to slave mode only)

utopiaBus16.name: utopiaBus16
utopiaBus16.description: UTOPIA interface mode of bus width

aTMPHYType.name: aTMPHYType
aTMPHYType.description: External interface type of the board

disablePayloadScrambling.name: disablePayloadScrambling
disablePayloadScrambling.description: Disable/Enable Cell payload scrambling in the ATM PHY

sendIdleCASUponLinkFail.name: sendIdleCASUponLinkFail
sendIdleCASUponLinkFail.description: This I.366.2 allows sending a special idle CAS packet which signals that the other side has a failure

vccProfile.name: vccProfile
vccProfile.description: Determine the required combination of Board's maximal number of VCC and maximal number of channels per VCC

tPNCPVPI.name: tPNCPVPI
tPNCPVPI.description: VPI used for transferring TPNCP command over AAL5 transport layer

tPNCPVCI.name: tPNCPVCI
tPNCPVCI.description: VCI used for transferring TPNCP command over AAL5 transport layer

acVpFile.name: acVpFile
acVpFile.description: The name (and path) of the file containing the voice prompts

acPolarityReversalType.name: acPolarityReversalType
acPolarityReversalType.description: Sets the type of the polarity reversal signal used for the network far-end answer and disconnect indications. Smooth reversal prevents negative effects as non-required ringing.

megacoCurrentProfile.name: megacoCurrentProfile
megacoCurrentProfile.description: Use this parameter to MGCP/MEGACO beheviour for specific compatibility. See user manual.

megacoGatewayName.name: megacoGatewayName
megacoGatewayName.description: MGCP:Gateway's identification name towards the MGCP Call Agent. If empty Gateway name holds the IP address of the board MEGACO: Prefix of the gateway part of the termination name

megacoTrunkName.name: megacoTrunkName
megacoTrunkName.description: MGCP: Together with 'EndpointPrefix' field generates local endpoint name on trunk enabled gateways MEGACO: Prefix of the trunk part of the termination name

megacoCheckLegalityOfMGC.name: megacoCheckLegalityOfMGC
megacoCheckLegalityOfMGC.description: This parameter specified if the MEGACO will reject commands from an MGC not in the provisioned list

megacoCallAgentPort.name: megacoCallAgentPort
megacoCallAgentPort.description: List of up to 10 UDP Ports of MEGACO Call Agent separated by , or ;.

acIsdnDuplicateQ931BuffMode.name: acIsdnDuplicateQ931BuffMode
acIsdnDuplicateQ931BuffMode.description: Activates / de-activates delivery of raw Q.931 messages. This Object is obsolete and is replaces by acTrunkISDNCommonDuplicateQ931BuffMode in the acPSTN-MIB.

acPSTNCASTableNum.name: acPSTNCASTableNum
acPSTNCASTableNum.description: Indicates how many CAS protocol configuration files are loaded, when 0 is no CAS table. It should match the number of fields.

amsNumOfConferencePorts.name: amsNumOfConferencePorts
amsNumOfConferencePorts.description: Number Of Conference ports. How many ports on the TPM are allocated to the conferencing service.

amsNumOfTestTrunkPorts.name: amsNumOfTestTrunkPorts
amsNumOfTestTrunkPorts.description: Number Of Test Trunk ports. How many ports on the TPM are allocated to the Test Trunk service.

amsNumOfLawfulInterceptPorts.name: amsNumOfLawfulInterceptPorts
amsNumOfLawfulInterceptPorts.description: Number Of Test Trunk ports. How many ports on the TPM are allocated to the Lawful Intercept service.

amsNumOfAnnouncementPorts.name: amsNumOfAnnouncementPorts
amsNumOfAnnouncementPorts.description: Number Of Test Trunk ports. How many ports on the TPM are allocated to the Announcement service.

amsApsIpAddress.name: amsApsIpAddress
amsApsIpAddress.description: Sets the destination IP to which the heartbeat packets are sent.

amsApsPort.name: amsApsPort
amsApsPort.description: Sets the destination UDP port to which the heartbeat packets are sent.

amsProfile.name: amsProfile
amsProfile.description: AMS Profile Bit Mask: 1'st bit - APS Audio Enable/Disable 2'nd bit - Trunks Interface On/Off 3'td bit - Board Operation State change on ATM Port failure Enable/Disable.

acFeatureKeyString.name: acFeatureKeyString
acFeatureKeyString.description: Coded Key specific for board and required features.

acDspVersionTemplate.name: acDspVersionTemplate
acDspVersionTemplate.description: selects the DSP load number, which defines the supported set of coders. Default=0 Each template assigns a specific version to each DSP. Each DSP version supports a set of coders and features. The number of channels supported by the DSP can also vary between DSP versions. The total number of channels supported by the board depends on the selected template.

acSysUpTime.name: acSysUpTime
acSysUpTime.description: Time (in Seconds) that the board is alive.

acBoardTemperature.name: acBoardTemperature
acBoardTemperature.description: Temperature of the board in degrees Celsius, should not go higher then 60!

voiceSettingsTable.name: voiceSettingsTable
voiceSettingsTable.description: Data in voice SettingsTable uniquely identify a voice parameters of channel.

pFE.name: pFE
pFE.description: Post Filter Enable of the voice coder

hPFE.name: hPFE
hPFE.description: High Pass Filter Enabled of the voice coder

testMode.name: testMode
testMode.description: Testing mode to be applied. Valid Range:CoderLoopback will perform an encoder-decoder loopback inside the DSP device, PCMLoopback will loopback the incoming PCM to the outgoing PCM, ToneInjection will generate a1000 Hz tone to outgoing PCM and NoLoopback will set the channel to work in a normal mode. Refer to TTestCode enumeration (default =3= NoLoopBack).

voiceVolume.name: voiceVolume
voiceVolume.description: Voice Volume sets the voice decoders output gain Range: 0-63 corresponding to -31 dB to +31 dB in 1 dB steps

inputGain.name: inputGain
inputGain.description: PCM input gain sets the gain at the encoders input.

m.name: m
m.description: This Packet Multiply Factor is the Number of 20 msec payloads (30 msec for G.723) to be used for generating one RTP packet. Range: 1 - Until max Tx/Rx buffer size is reached

rTPRedundancyDepth.name: rTPRedundancyDepth
rTPRedundancyDepth.description: RTP Redundancy Depth. Number of repetitions to be applied to each RTP payload when transmitting to network. apply redundancy sequence per RFC2198. Valid range: Disable redundancy packets generation = 0. Enable generation of RFC2198 redundancy packets = 1.

eCLength.name: eCLength
eCLength.description: Length of echo canceler tail to be used according to TECLength enumeration. Note that EC length has different length limitations for different boards.

eCHybridLoss.name: eCHybridLoss
eCHybridLoss.description: Echo Cancler Hybrid Loss. sets the worst case ratio between the signal level transmitted to the hybrid and the echo level returning from the hybrid. User should set this value according to the worst hybrid in the system in terms of echo return loss according to enum TECHybridLoss enumeration

faxModemSettingsTable.name: faxModemSettingsTable
faxModemSettingsTable.description: Data in faxModem Settings Table uniquely identify fax and modem parameters channel.

faxRelayMaxRate.name: faxRelayMaxRate
faxRelayMaxRate.description: Fax Relay Max Rate Limits the maximum rate at which fax messages are transmitted. Refer to acTFaxModemRelayRate enumeration. (Default =14400 bps).

modemRelayMaxRate.name: modemRelayMaxRate
modemRelayMaxRate.description: Modem Relay Max Rate Limits the maximum rate at which modem relay messages are transmitted. Refer to acTFaxModemRelayRate enumeration. (Default =14400 bps).

faxRelayECMEnable.name: faxRelayECMEnable
faxRelayECMEnable.description: Fax Relay ECM Enable Enable using ECM mode during Fax Relay.

t38FaxRelayProtectionMode.name: t38FaxRelayProtectionMode
t38FaxRelayProtectionMode.description: T38 Fax Relay Protection Mode Use Forward Error Correction (FEC) algorithm to protect T.38 fax relay stream.

faxRelayRedundancyDepth.name: faxRelayRedundancyDepth
faxRelayRedundancyDepth.description: Fax Relay Redundancy Depth Number of repetitions to be applied to each fax relay payload when transmitting to network (applicable only when acTFaxModemCmdacTFaxModemSettings.T38FaxRelayProtectionMode=0).

enhancedFaxRelayRedundancyDepth.name: enhancedFaxRelayRedundancyDepth
enhancedFaxRelayRedundancyDepth.description: Enhanced Fax Relay Redundancy Depth Number of repetitions to be applied to control packets when using T.38 standard.

modemRelayRedundancyDepth.name: modemRelayRedundancyDepth
modemRelayRedundancyDepth.description: Modem Relay Redundancy Depth Number of repetitions to be applied to each modem relay payload when transmitting to network.

faxModemRelayVolume.name: faxModemRelayVolume
faxModemRelayVolume.description: Fax Modem Relay Volume Fax gain control. Range: -18 - 15 corresponding to -18.5 dBm to -3.5 dBm in 1 dB steps. The reason the range extends to 15 is for backward compatibility. (Default =6).

faxModemBypassCoderType.name: faxModemBypassCoderType
faxModemBypassCoderType.description: Fax Modem Bypass Coder Type Coder to be used while performing fax/modem bypass. Usually, high bit rate coders such as G.711 and G.726/G.727 should be used. (Default = G.711 A-law).

faxModemBypassM.name: faxModemBypassM
faxModemBypassM.description: Fax Modem Bypass M Number of 20 msec payloads to be used for generating one RTP fax/modem bypass packet. Range: 1 - Until max Tx/Rx buffer size is reached

useT38orFRF11.name: useT38orFRF11
useT38orFRF11.description: Use T38 or FRF11 Use T.38 protocol or proprietary FRF.11 syntax, to send/receive fax relay.

dJBSettingsTable.name: dJBSettingsTable
dJBSettingsTable.description: Data in dJB Settings Table uniquely identify jitter buffer parameters of channel.

dJBufOptFactor.name: dJBufOptFactor
dJBufOptFactor.description: Dynamic Jitter Buffer Optimization Factor. Dynamic jitter buffer frame error/delay optimization. 0 - 12 (default =7)

channelTDMBusSettingsTable.name: channelTDMBusSettingsTable
channelTDMBusSettingsTable.description: Data in channel TDM Bus Settings Table, uniquely identify TDM Bus sparameters of channel

tDMBusInputPort.name: tDMBusInputPort
tDMBusInputPort.description: TDM Bus Input Port. Together with TDMBusInputChannel, defines the TDM bus timeslot to be used as input for this channel. Note that the valid region for this parameter varies according to the type of TDM bus used. When using TDMBusType=acFramers this parameter selects the trunkID, in which the incoming B-channel resides. 0-127.

tDMBusInputChannel.name: tDMBusInputChannel
tDMBusInputChannel.description: TDM Bus Input Channel. Together with TDMBusInputPort, defines the TDM bus timeslot to be used as input for this channel. Note that the valid region for this parameter varies according to the TDMBusSpeed. When using TDMBusType=acFramers, this parameter selects the incoming B-channel (in this case the valid region is 0-31).

tDMBusOutputDisable.name: tDMBusOutputDisable
tDMBusOutputDisable.description: TDM Bus Output Disable. 0: Places TDM bus output timeslot in tri-state mode. Ignored in case of PSTN interface. 1: Enables TDM bus output timeslot. Ignored in case of PSTN interface.

tDMBusOutputPort.name: tDMBusOutputPort
tDMBusOutputPort.description: TDM Bus Output Port. Together with TDMBusOutputChannel, defines the TDM bus timeslot to be used as output for this channel. Note that the valid region for this parameter varies according to the type of TDM bus used. When this parameter is set to 0xff=255 the boardwise setting (set in acOpenBoard()) will be used. When using TDMBusType=acFramers, this parameter is ignored. 0-31 or 255.

tDMBusOutputChannel.name: tDMBusOutputChannel
tDMBusOutputChannel.description: TDM Bus Output Channel. Together with TDMBusOutputPort, defines the TDM bus timeslot to be used as output for this channel. Note that the valid region for this parameter varies according to the TDMBusSpeed. When using TDMBusType=acFramers, this parameter is ignored.

transportSettingsTable.name: transportSettingsTable
transportSettingsTable.description: Data in Transport Table, uniquely identify Transport sparameters of channel.

useNIorPCI.name: useNIorPCI
useNIorPCI.description: Description: Use NI or PCI interface. =1 if channel will use NI interface, =0 if PCI interface. 0- PCI interface: Compressed traffic will be sent/received through the PCI interface. 1- NI interface: RTP-RTCP packets sent/received to/from on board Ethernet interface. (default=1).

disableSoftIPLoopback.name: disableSoftIPLoopback
disableSoftIPLoopback.description: Disable Soft IP Loopback =1 in order to diable soft IP loopback. 0- Enables the hair pin connection made in case two channels on the same board are connected together. 1- Disables the hair pin connection made in case two channels on the same board are connected together.

uniDirectionalRTP.name: uniDirectionalRTP
uniDirectionalRTP.description: uni Directional RTP. enables one sided RTP stream - according to niDirectionalRTPMode. enables the User to set the channel to work with unidirectional RTP streams. When UniDirectionalRTP is set to acRTPTxOnly, the receiver part of the channel will be disabled, and only the transmitter (encoder) will work. When UniDirectionalRTP is set to acRTPRxOnly, the transmitter part of the channel will be disabled, and only the receiver (decoder) will work. When UniDirectionalRTP is set to acRTPTxRx, both sides will be enabled. Users should note that when configuring a session between two endpoints, some of the channel configuration parameters must be identical on both sides. Such parameters are the voice coder type, the Fax/Modem transport type and bypass coders. All other configuration parameters are independent.

rTPRTCPSettingsTable.name: rTPRTCPSettingsTable
rTPRTCPSettingsTable.description: Data in RTP-RTCP Table, uniquely identify RTP-RTCP sparameters of channel.

cNAME.name: cNAME
cNAME.description: RTP Canonical Name. Should be unique among all participants within one RTP session. Refer to RFC1890 for more information. Up to 255 characters string. (default ='ChX', X=CID).

iPPrecedence.name: iPPrecedence
iPPrecedence.description: IP Precedence. Sets the value of the IP precedence field in the IP header for all the packets to be generated from this channel. Follow the acTIPPrecedence enumeration. Valid Range: 0-7 (default =0)

iPTOS.name: iPTOS
iPTOS.description: iP Type Of Service. sets the value of the IP Type Of Service field in the IP header for all the packets to be generated from this channel. acNormalServiceTOS=0, acMinimizeMonetaryCostTOS=1, acMaximizeReliabilityTOS=2, acMaximizeThroughputTOS=4, acMinimizeDelayTOS=8 (Follow the acTIPTOS enumeration).

localRTPPort.name: localRTPPort
localRTPPort.description: Local RTP Port. Local UDP Port to be used for incoming RTP stream to this channel. This parameter also sets the local RTCP and local T.38 ports in offset of 1,2 from LocalRTPPort respectively. The local RTP port must be a number dividable by 10 and must reside within the following range BoardParams.BaseUDPPort-> BoardParams.BaseUDPPort +10*MAX_CID_NUM.

remoteRTPPort.name: remoteRTPPort
remoteRTPPort.description: IP/UDP Address of the remote endpoint RTP port

remoteT38Port.name: remoteT38Port
remoteT38Port.description: IP/UDP Address of the remote endpoint T.38 port

rTCPMeanTxInterval.name: rTCPMeanTxInterval
rTCPMeanTxInterval.description: RTCP Mean Tx Interval. Mean interval [msec] between channel's RTCP reports.

rxRTPPayloadType.name: rxRTPPayloadType
rxRTPPayloadType.description: Rx RTP Payload Type -1 = use the default coder RTP payload type for incoming voice packets. -2 = allow any RTP payload type for incoming packets. Otherwise, = sets the RTP payload type to be used for incoming voice packets (this will override the default RTP payload type defined for each coder). Valid Range: -1/-2 or any unoccupied RTPPT in the range 0-127 . (default =-1).

txRTPPayloadType.name: txRTPPayloadType
txRTPPayloadType.description: Tx RTP Payload Type -1 = use the default coder RTP payload type for incoming voice packets. -2 = allow any RTP payload type for incoming packets. Otherwise, = sets the RTP payload type to be used for incoming voice packets (this will override the default RTP payload type defined for each coder). Valid Range: -1/-2 or any unoccupied RTPPT in the range 0-127. (default =-1).

channelStatusTable.name: channelStatusTable
channelStatusTable.description: Data in voice SettingsTable uniquely identify a voice parameters of channel.

jitterBufAccumDelay.name: jitterBufAccumDelay
jitterBufAccumDelay.description: Jitter Buffer accumulation Delay. In packets.

fXSorFXO.name: fXSorFXO
fXSorFXO.description: returns the type phisical type of endpoint

remoteReset.name: remoteReset
remoteReset.description: remote Reset. To remote reset the board, set an integer value to this parameter. Note: Before Reset, The current boardConfiguration parameters will be burned to the board.

acSetDefaults.name: acSetDefaults
acSetDefaults.description: To set the default values, set an integer value to this parameter

acgwAdminState.name: acgwAdminState
acgwAdminState.description: Determines the gateway's operational state. 0 - locked: Shutdown the GW In the time frame set by acgwAdminStateLockControl 1 - shuttingDown: (read only) Graceful Shutdown is being carried out 2 - unlocked: GW is in service.

acgwAdminStateLockControl.name: acgwAdminStateLockControl
acgwAdminStateLockControl.description: (in sec) time left for the graceful shutdown to complete. -1 indicates unlimited time frame. 0 indicates immediate (forced) lock. Implementing the control requires setting acgwAdminState to locked.

acSaveConfigToSystem.name: acSaveConfigToSystem
acSaveConfigToSystem.description: This will save all current configuration in the board onto the flash. Any digit will call on the function. NOTE: Do NOT save the configuration while voice is running - this will cause a delay.

acOperationalState.name: acOperationalState
acOperationalState.description: The operational state of the gateway.

remoteResetControl.name: remoteResetControl
remoteResetControl.description: Determine the remote reset action 1 - burn staged load image, if any, and config to flash, perform a reset, and load from flash 2 - perform a reset, and load from flash (staged load image, if any, and config is not burned to flash) 3 - perform a reset, and load from bootp/tftp (staged load image, if any, and config burn is not needed) * - an error is returned for any other value Note: The staged load image is an image of a cmp file that was previously loaded to a area in RAM via an HTTP upload

acBoardTrapGlobalsUniqID.name: acBoardTrapGlobalsUniqID
acBoardTrapGlobalsUniqID.description: Trap Uniq Id - generated by AcBoard and should be uniq for the entire EMS

acBoardTrapGlobalsDateAndTime.name: acBoardTrapGlobalsDateAndTime
acBoardTrapGlobalsDateAndTime.description: Date and time that the trap was sent.

acBoardTemperatureAlarm.name: acBoardTemperatureAlarm
acBoardTemperatureAlarm.description: Temperature Alarm. Turned on when temperature exceeds 60 degrees Celsius, and relaxes when temperature goes under 55 again.

acBoardEvResettingBoard.name: acBoardEvResettingBoard
acBoardEvResettingBoard.description: The board start Reset process - following software reset

acgwAdminStateChange.name: acgwAdminStateChange
acgwAdminStateChange.description: The administrative state of the gate way has been changed to a new state.

acBoardControllerFailureAlarm.name: acBoardControllerFailureAlarm
acBoardControllerFailureAlarm.description: The GK/Proxy not found or registration failed. internal routing table may be used for routing

acBoardEthernetLinkAlarm.name: acBoardEthernetLinkAlarm
acBoardEthernetLinkAlarm.description: Ethernet Link is down or remote Ethernet link is down and board has no communication to any other host

acBoardOverloadAlarm.name: acBoardOverloadAlarm
acBoardOverloadAlarm.description: Overload in one or some of the system's components

acActiveAlarmTableOverflow.name: acActiveAlarmTableOverflow
acActiveAlarmTableOverflow.description: An active alarm could not be placed in the active alarm table because the table is full. This alarm will not clear. Reboot is the only way to completely clear the Active Alarm table overflow problem. Any alarm raised at this state will not be Carrier Grade compatible. Therefore, Updates will not clear the alarm before changing the bindings and re-raising alarms. The History tables remain unaffected. All Alarms raised prior to overflow will remain Carrier Grade compatible. Other alarms, raised after this alarm was raised, that are placed in the Active Alarm table will be Carrier Grade compatible. (This is for when after the alarm was raised there were some clears, clearing alarms off the Active Alarm table).

acAudioProvisioningAlarm.name: acAudioProvisioningAlarm
acAudioProvisioningAlarm.description: This alarm is raised if the Media Server is unable to provision its audio. This could be because the Audio Provisioning System (APS) is down or there is a network problem.

acOperationalStateChange.name: acOperationalStateChange
acOperationalStateChange.description: This alarm is raised if the operational state of the node goes to disabled. The alarm is cleared when the operational state of the node goes to enabled.

acKeepAlive.name: acKeepAlive
acKeepAlive.description: This trap is the NAT Traversal keep alive trap. If the STUN application in the device detects a NAT then this trap will be sent out on a regular time laps - 9/10 of the acSysSTUNBindingLifeTime object. The AdditionalInfo1 varbind has the MAC address of the device. Note that all traps are sent out from the SNMP Port (usually 161).

acNATTraversalAlarm.name: acNATTraversalAlarm
acNATTraversalAlarm.description: When the NAT placed in front a device is identified as a symmetric NAT - this alarm is raised. It is cleared when a non-symmetric NAT or no NAT replace the symmetric one.

acEnhancedBITStatus.name: acEnhancedBITStatus
acEnhancedBITStatus.description: This trap is used to for the status of the BIT (Built In Test). The information in the trap contains board HW elements being tested and their status. The information is presented in the additional info fields.

acSS7LinkStateChangeAlarm.name: acSS7LinkStateChangeAlarm
acSS7LinkStateChangeAlarm.description: This alarm is raised if the operational state of the SS7 link becomes XXXX. The alarm is cleared when the operational state of the link becomes XXXX.

acSS7LinkInhibitStateChangeAlarm.name: acSS7LinkInhibitStateChangeAlarm
acSS7LinkInhibitStateChangeAlarm.description: This alarm is raised if the SS7 link becomes inhibited (local or remote). The alarm is cleared when the link becomes uninhibited - local AND remote. Note that this alarm will be raised for any change in the remote or local inhibition status.

acSS7LinkBlockStateChangeAlarm.name: acSS7LinkBlockStateChangeAlarm
acSS7LinkBlockStateChangeAlarm.description: This alarm is raised if the SS7 link becomes blocked (local or remote). The alarm is cleared when the link becomes unblocked - local AND remote. Note that this alarm will be raised for any change in the remote or local blocking status.

acSS7LinkCongestionStateChangeAlarm.name: acSS7LinkCongestionStateChangeAlarm
acSS7LinkCongestionStateChangeAlarm.description: This alarm is raised if the SS7 link becomes congested (local or remote). The alarm is cleared when the link becomes uncongested - local AND remote. Note that this alarm will be raised for any change in the remote or local congestion status.

acSS7LinkSetStateChangeAlarm.name: acSS7LinkSetStateChangeAlarm
acSS7LinkSetStateChangeAlarm.description: This alarm is raised if the operational state of the SS7 linkset becomes BUSY. The alarm is cleared when the operational state of the linkset becomes IN-SERVICE or OFFLINE.

acSS7RouteSetStateChangeAlarm.name: acSS7RouteSetStateChangeAlarm
acSS7RouteSetStateChangeAlarm.description: This alarm is raised if the operational state of the SS7 routeset becomes BUSY. The alarm is cleared when the operational state of the routeset becomes IN-SERVICE or OFFLINE.

acSS7SNSetStateChangeAlarm.name: acSS7SNSetStateChangeAlarm
acSS7SNSetStateChangeAlarm.description: This alarm is raised if the operational state of the SS7 node becomes BUSY. The alarm is cleared when the operational state of the node becomes IN-SERVICE or OFFLINE.

acSS7RedundancyAlarm.name: acSS7RedundancyAlarm
acSS7RedundancyAlarm.description: Raised when the SS7 redundancy degregated. Cleared when all entities of redundancy are fully functional and in serveice.

acPerformanceMonitoringThresholdCrossing.name: acPerformanceMonitoringThresholdCrossing
acPerformanceMonitoringThresholdCrossing.description: This log trap is sent out for every time the threshold of a Performance Monitored object is crossed. The severity field is 'indeterminate' when the crossing is above the threshold and 'cleared' when it goes back under the threshold. The 'source' varbind in the trap indicates the object for which the threshold is being crossed.

acHTTPDownloadResult.name: acHTTPDownloadResult
acHTTPDownloadResult.description: This trap indicates the result of a recent file download (includes HTTP error code, if available).

acFanTrayAlarm.name: acFanTrayAlarm
acFanTrayAlarm.description: This alarm is raised when the fan tray is missing or some of the fans are faulty. If the fan tray is missing or more then X fans are faulty the severity will be Critical. If more then one and less the X fans are faulty the severity will be Major.

acPowerSupplyAlarm.name: acPowerSupplyAlarm
acPowerSupplyAlarm.description: This alarm is raised when the HA (High Availability) feature is active and one of the power supply units is faulty.

acPEMAlarm.name: acPEMAlarm
acPEMAlarm.description: This alarm is raised when the HA (High Availability) feature is active. The severity is critical if one of the PEM units is missing and major if the electric wire to one of the units is disconnected.

acSAMissingAlarm.name: acSAMissingAlarm
acSAMissingAlarm.description: This alarm is raised when the SA module in the M3K MG is missing. Whenthere is no SAT there are no other chassis HW related alarms. Note - relevant only for M3K.

acHASystemFaultAlarm.name: acHASystemFaultAlarm
acHASystemFaultAlarm.description: This alarm is raised when the HA (High Availability) feature is active and the system is NOT HA. Critical severity - 1.Wrong HW Configuration. 2. Redundant module is missing (not in slot). 3. The redundant module is non operable. Minor severity - waiting for redunadant to connect (after reset!).

acHASystemConfigMismatchAlarm.name: acHASystemConfigMismatchAlarm
acHASystemConfigMismatchAlarm.description: This alarm is raised when the HA (High Availability) feature is active and there has been a configuration change due to which the HA system may or may not be usable.

acHASystemSwitchOverAlarm.name: acHASystemSwitchOverAlarm
acHASystemSwitchOverAlarm.description: This alarm is raised when the HA (High Availability) feature is active and there has been a switchover due to failure or reset in the active module.

acUserInputAlarm.name: acUserInputAlarm
acUserInputAlarm.description: This Alarm is raised when the input dry contact is short circuited. Cleared when the circuit is reopened.

acDChannelStatus.name: acDChannelStatus
acDChannelStatus.description: This non alarm trap is sent when establishment, re-establishment or release of LAPD link with its peer connection occurs. The trap will be sent out with one of the following in the textual description: D-channel synchronized D-channel not-synchronized

acSonetSectionLOFAlarm.name: acSonetSectionLOFAlarm
acSonetSectionLOFAlarm.description: SONET section Loss of Frame alarm.

acSonetSectionLOSAlarm.name: acSonetSectionLOSAlarm
acSonetSectionLOSAlarm.description: SONET section Loss of Signal alarm.

acSonetIfHwFailureAlarm.name: acSonetIfHwFailureAlarm
acSonetIfHwFailureAlarm.description: SONET or SDH medium Interface has failed.

acH248LostConnectionWithCA.name: acH248LostConnectionWithCA
acH248LostConnectionWithCA.description: H248 lost connection with call agent

acHitlessUpdateStatus.name: acHitlessUpdateStatus
acHitlessUpdateStatus.description: Notification trap that is sent out at the beginning and the end of a Hitless SW update. Failure during the process will also instigate the trap. Relevant to HA systems only.

acTrunksAlarmNearEndLOS.name: acTrunksAlarmNearEndLOS
acTrunksAlarmNearEndLOS.description: Loss of signal at trunk's near end.

acTrunksAlarmNearEndLOF.name: acTrunksAlarmNearEndLOF
acTrunksAlarmNearEndLOF.description: Loss of frame at trunk's near end.

acTrunksAlarmRcvAIS.name: acTrunksAlarmRcvAIS
acTrunksAlarmRcvAIS.description: Received AIS from trunk's far end.

acTrunksAlarmFarEndLOF.name: acTrunksAlarmFarEndLOF
acTrunksAlarmFarEndLOF.description: Loss of frame at trunk's far end.

acIPv6ErrorAlarm.name: acIPv6ErrorAlarm
acIPv6ErrorAlarm.description: Alarm trap that is sent out for IPv6 related errors.

acWeakRedundancy.name: acWeakRedundancy
acWeakRedundancy.description: The system is in weak redundancy mode. Switch over is done with a reset to the board taking over.

acTMInconsistentRemoteAndLocalPLLStatus.name: acTMInconsistentRemoteAndLocalPLLStatus
acTMInconsistentRemoteAndLocalPLLStatus.description: Inconsistent Remote And Local PLL Status

acGWSASEmergencyModeAlarm.name: acGWSASEmergencyModeAlarm
acGWSASEmergencyModeAlarm.description: The alarm is raised when SAS enters the Emergency Mode and then cleared when SAS enters Normal Mode again.

acV52InterfaceAlarm.name: acV52InterfaceAlarm
acV52InterfaceAlarm.description: The alarm is raised for v5.2 interface errors and alarms.{@}For a detailed list of the interfaces' alarms see the acV5InterfceTable.

acSonetPathSignalLabelMismatchAlarm.name: acSonetPathSignalLabelMismatchAlarm
acSonetPathSignalLabelMismatchAlarm.description: Sonet Path Signal Label Mismatch alarm.

acSWUpgradeAlarm.name: acSWUpgradeAlarm
acSWUpgradeAlarm.description: Raised for SW upgrade process errors.

acNTPServerStatusAlarm.name: acNTPServerStatusAlarm
acNTPServerStatusAlarm.description: NTP server status alarm. {@}Raised when the connection to the NTP server is lost. Cleared when the connection is reestablished. {@}Unset time (as a result of no connection to NTP server) may result with functionality degradation and failure in device.

acThreeWayConferenceOutOfResources.name: acThreeWayConferenceOutOfResources
acThreeWayConferenceOutOfResources.description: Three way conference out of resources.

acSS7AliasPcStateChangeAlarm.name: acSS7AliasPcStateChangeAlarm
acSS7AliasPcStateChangeAlarm.description: raised when the Alias PC is in BUSY state. Cleared when it is in In-Service state.

acSS7UalGroupStateChangeAlarm.name: acSS7UalGroupStateChangeAlarm
acSS7UalGroupStateChangeAlarm.description: Raised when the Ual Group Asp state is not ACTIVE. Cleared when it is Active.

acLDAPLostConnection.name: acLDAPLostConnection
acLDAPLostConnection.description: Raised when there is no connection to the LDAP server.

acAnalogPortGroundFaultOutOfService.name: acAnalogPortGroundFaultOutOfService
acAnalogPortGroundFaultOutOfService.description: Raised when the MP500 FXS port is inactive due to ground fault.

acSSHConnectionStatus.name: acSSHConnectionStatus
acSSHConnectionStatus.description: This trap indicates the result of a recent SSH connection attempt.

acOCSPServerStatusAlarm.name: acOCSPServerStatusAlarm
acOCSPServerStatusAlarm.description: raised when OCSP connection is not available.
